<%= erb :header %>
<div class="ui list">
  <div class="item">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="header">Secret does not exist</div>
      It might be caused by any of these reasons
    </div>
    <div class="list">
      <div class="item">
        <i class="unhide outline icon"></i>
        <div class="content">
          <a class="header">Opened before</a>
          <div class="description">A secret can only be displayed ONCE. It might be lost due to a non-techy sender that clicked the URL before sending it to you. The secret might have been compromised and read by someone else. You should contact the sender and request a new secret</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="item">
        <i class="unlink outline icon"></i>
        <div class="content">
          <a class="header">Incorrect URL</a>
          <div class="description">The URL you've been given might be missing some magic digits</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="item">
        <i class="time icon"></i>
        <div class="content">
          <a class="header">Expired secret</a>
          <div class="description">No secrets last forever. All secrets expires automatically. Lifetime varies from one hour up to one week</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="item">
        <i class="warning icon"></i>
        <div class="content">
          <a class="header">Server Restart</a>
          <div class="description">No secrets are stored on disk, which means that all secrets will be lost if Yopass is restarted for some reason</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
<%= erb :footer %>
